00:00:01.650 --> 00:00:09.440
&gt;&gt; From the Library of Congress in Washington,
D.C.

00:00:09.440 --> 00:00:15.559
In today's complicated political environment,
one thing is certain - you need to know the

00:00:15.559 --> 00:00:16.559
facts.

00:00:16.559 --> 00:00:21.449
Where do you go to find -
What bills your Representative or Senator

00:00:21.449 --> 00:00:23.009
introduced.

00:00:23.009 --> 00:00:25.119
Current information about tax proposals.

00:00:25.119 --> 00:00:28.970
Historical information about health care legislation.

00:00:28.970 --> 00:00:34.750
Explanations of the legislative process and
current legislative activities.

00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:40.380
For nearly two decades, the Library of Congress
has provided the nation's lawmakers, the American

00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:47.210
People, and the world with free access to
non-biased and reliable legislative information.

00:00:47.210 --> 00:00:53.030
But changing technology demands that system
evolve to keep up with how information is

00:00:53.030 --> 00:00:54.650
accessed today.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:01:01.240
The new Congress.gov is user friendly, easy-to-search
and makes legislative information more mobile

00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:02.940
and shareable.

00:01:02.940 --> 00:01:11.490
Whether you are a concerned citizen, journalist,
educator, student, or member of Congress...you

00:01:11.490 --> 00:01:17.340
can see democracy at work-Congress.gov-Informing
Democracy.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:20.990
This has been a presentation of the Library
of Congress.

00:01:20.990 --> 00:01:23.329
Visit us at loc.gov.

